Among the 13 cities that have less than 50 cases, 9 cities located in the Northern China with average AT below 0 °C, 12 cities had average AH below 4 g/m3 and one city (Haikou) had the highest AH (14.05 g/m3) (Fig. 1, Fig. 2
and Table 1
). The MSI in these 13 cities were relatively lower than the remaining 17 cities that have more than 50 cases (Fig. 2).
